<p style="text-indent: 2em;">On January 25, JD Cloud announced that JD Cloud RDS formally supported MySQL version 8.0 in all regions. MySQL 8.0 is the latest version of the MySQL community, which compared to MySQL 5.7, it has supported more new features, significantly updated and optimized the existing features, and significantly improved performance. The initial release of MySQL version 8.0 by JD Cloud this time not only proves the R&D strength and innovation capability of JD Cloud technology team, but also shows that JD Cloud hopes to reward users through more high-quality cloud computing services and help users use new technologies to innovate and implement more business values.</p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;"><br/></p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;">Major benefits and features of MySQL version 8.0 include:</p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;"><br/></p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;"><strong>Document Storage</strong></p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;"><br/></p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;">This new feature supported by MySQL 8.0 is a milestone without doubt. If you are developing a document service, now a database can meet your needs at one time.</p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;"><br/></p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;"><strong>Performance</strong></p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;"><br/></p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;">MySQL 8.0 has optimized performance of scenarios for Read and Write working load, I/O-bound working load and "hot-spot" working load with high competition, which improves the replication performance. And it also provides resource group function, which can run on designated hardware CPU for special user threads so as to achieve the goal of performance optimization. In terms of index performance, it has supported descending index. As a result, we need not to call order by command to read the values of a certain index in a table and output them in descending order.</p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;"><br/></p>
