<p style="text-indent: 2em;"><strong>Security</strong></p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;"><br/></p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;">MySQL version 8.0 supports SQL roles through which permissions can be controlled. And take OpenSSL as the default TLS/SSL library. Support to customize Round Robin policy of database password, including password expiration time, password strength, etc, to strengthen user password security protection.</p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;"><br/></p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;"><strong>Reliability</strong></p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;"><br/></p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;">MySQL Version 8.0 support atom, Data Definition Language (DDL) with crash security, and the original two data dictionaries have been merged into one.</p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;"><br/></p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;"><strong>Manageability</strong></p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;"><br/></p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;">Support invisible index. The column name renaming (SQL DDL) feature was optimized for MySQL 8.0 compared to the processing method of MySQL version 5.7.</p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;"><br/></p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;"><strong>Provide More Powerful JSON Support</strong></p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;"><br/></p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;">MySQL version 8.0 provides even more powerful support to JSON, allowing JSON_TABLE() functions to convert data with JSON format into relational table storage. Support -&gt;&gt; operational characters, which is equal to calling JSON_UNQUOTE(JSON_EXTRACT()). Support two new aggregation functions &nbsp;JSON_ARRAYAGG() and JSON_OBJECTAGG(). Provide practical tools such as JSON_PRETTY(), JSON_STORAGE_SIZE() and JSON_STORAGE_FREE(), among which JSON_PRETTY() can print and display the JSON object via an easy and readable method. Partial in-place updates are supported for the values of the JSON objects, and the sorting has been optimized to provide higher performance.</p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;"><br/></p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;"><strong>GIS</strong></p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;"><br/></p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;">Support spatial data type, index and function, which can support 5,108 different spatial reference systems, including 4,628 projections (plan), 479 earth geography (ellipse) expressions and 1 Descartes universal abstract plane.</p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;"><br/></p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;"><strong>Window Function+Public Table Expression</strong></p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;"><br/></p>
<p style="text-indent: 2em;">MySQL version 8.0 supports window function feature and public table expression, of which window function can reduce the coding complexity so as to improve the production efficiency. Public table expression (with search) reduces the complexity of search.</p>
